			<h3 class="first"><a href="#p113465">Will 2 lighthouses work for what I need? (Diagram included.)</a></h3>
			<p class="author"><a href="./viewtopic.php?p=113465&amp;sid=cc8feaff7adf767811dcf78d6ff6e4f1#p113465"><img src="./styles/robotreviews/imageset/icon_post_target.gif" width="11" height="9" alt="Post" title="Post" /></a>by <strong><a href="./memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=21151&amp;sid=cc8feaff7adf767811dcf78d6ff6e4f1">carwashguy</a></strong> &raquo; January 24th, 2013, 12:23 pm </p>

			

			<div class="content">Here is the layout of my house:<br /><br /><img src="http://i.imgur.com/pDrn5lD.png" alt="Image" /><br /><br />I'm getting a Roomba 780. I was wondering how I might get it to clean every room in my house automatically on a schedule. Will the two lighthouses that it comes with be enough? I've marked on the diagram two red circles where I think I should put them. If not, where, how many more should I get, and is it possible to use none at all with any success? I appreciate any insight you could give me at all.</div>

			

		</div>

		
